title: How Black socialite Mollie Moon raised millions to fund the civil rights movement
description: Historian Tanisha Ford tells the story of the Harlem activist credited with raising millions to build economic and racial equality in the U.S. Ford's new book is Our Secret Society.

title: It's unlikely, but not impossible, to limit global warming to 1.5 Celsius, study finds
description: Humans are still pumping enormous amounts of carbon dioxide into the atmosphere. That puts this decade's climate goals further out of reach.

title: The UAW reaches a tentative deal with GM, the last holdout of Detroit's Big 3
description: Record deals with all three unionized automakers means a historic 6-week strike is ending — for now. The deals still need to be ratified by members, who could choose to go back to the table.

title: Judge reimposes gag order on Trump in federal election interference case
description: The ruling puts back in place the restrictions that bar Trump from making public statements targeting prosecutors, court staff and likely witnesses.

title: Israel presses into Gaza as pro-Palestinian protests spread worldwide
description: An airport in southern Russia closed overnight after a crowd of protesters stormed the tarmac upon the arrival of a flight from Tel Aviv. An official called the riot a "gross violation of law."
